  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a comparison of the functional results and Varus-Valgus Stability in Single-radius
      versus Multi-radius Femoral Component for Total Knee Arthroplasty.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Recently, femoral designs based on a sagittal single radius were designed to allow better
      mid-flexion stability and extensor function after total knee arthroplasty. The purpose of
      this study was to compare mid-flexion stability and clinical outcomes in patients that
      received TKA using either a single-radius femoral design or multi-radius femoral design.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
